Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log

Class PositionAwarePhysicalFlushableChecksumChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log.PositionAwarePhysicalFlushableChecksumChannel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, ChecksumWriter, FlushableChannel, FlushableChecksumChannel, WritableChannel, WritableChecksumChannel, FlushablePositionAwareChecksumChannel, PositionAwareChannel
    public class PositionAwarePhysicalFlushableChecksumChannel
extends Object
implements FlushablePositionAwareChecksumChannel
    Decorator around a LogVersionedStoreChannel making it expose FlushablePositionAwareChecksumChannel. This implementation uses a PhysicalFlushableChecksumChannel, which provides buffering for write operations over the decorated channel.

      • prepareForFlush

        public Flushable prepareForFlush()
                          throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: FlushableChannel
        Ensures that all written content will be present in the file channel. This method does not flush, it prepares for it, by returning a handle for flushing at a later time. The returned handle guarantees that the writes that happened before its creation will be flushed. Implementations may choose to flush content that was written after a call to this method was made.
        Specified by:
        prepareForFlush in interface FlushableChannel
